{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01BUTqcMGMsNTPqA2JpLoKCW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01M74LfciYA9TKVC7XhKQsHm","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Heirloom Tomato Salad.generated.24.txt","content":"minutes in the oven. Turn the heat down to 180°C (350°F) and bake for\nanother 20-25 minutes until the meringue is crispy on the outside but\nstill soft in the middle. Remove from the oven and let cool slowly—\nrapid cooling can cause the meringue to crack and weep.\n\nDecorate the top with fresh raspberries or strawberries just before\nserving. A dollop of whipped cream on the side makes it even more\nindulgent. This dessert is best served within 2 hours of making, while\nthe contrast between crispy meringue and soft interior is still evident.\n\nHEIRLOOM TOMATO SALAD\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 1kg mixed heirloom tomatoes (various colors: red, yellow, orange, green)\n- 150g fresh mozzarella or burrata cheese\n- ¼ cup fresh basil leaves, roughly torn\n- ¼ cup fresh mint leaves\n- 3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil\n- 1½ tablespoons aged balsamic vinegar\n- 1 clove garlic, minced very finely\n- ½ teaspoon sea salt\n- ¼ teaspoon cracked black pepper\n- 1 shallot, thinly sliced\n- 50g Parmesan cheese, in thin shards\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Wash tomatoes and pat dry. Cut larger ones into wedges or thick\nslices, leave smaller ones whole. Arrange on a large serving platter,\nvarying the cuts and colors for visual interest.\n\n2. Tear mozzarella or burrata into bite-sized pieces and scatter over\nthe tomatoes.\n\n3. Whisk together olive oil, balsamic vinegar, minced garlic, salt, and\npepper in a small bowl. Let dressing sit for 5 minutes to allow flavors\nto meld.\n\n4. Drizzle dressing over the tomatoes and cheese. Scatter shallot slices,\nbasil, and mint over the top.\n\n5. Top with Parmesan shards. Serve immediately at room temperature. This\nsalad is best enjoyed on the day it is made when the tomatoes are at\ntheir sweetest and the cheese is creamy."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":845,"cache_read_input_tokens":105952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":845},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6b5fbce-18cb-479d-8d88-154976bac39e","uuid":"d6cbc94f-1527-4567-85b6-bf2da3627f56"}
