{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_016DyPUi5ALPKPh7prhxdv4e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013qGVZYtGR8W7sK4Ce96xt6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Ginger Lemon Tea.generated.24.txt","content":"GINGER LEMON TEA\n\nWhen winter winds blow cold and the days grow short, this warming infusion brings comfort\nand vitality to weary spirits. The bright notes of fresh lemon cut through the peppery heat\nof ginger, while honey adds a soothing sweetness. This tea has been cherished for centuries\nin Asian cuisines for both its warming properties and its ability to soothe the digestive system.\nA simple cup can transform a dreary afternoon into a moment of pure wellness.\n\nINGREDIENTS (makes 2 cups):\n- 1 piece fresh ginger root, about 2 inches long, peeled and thinly sliced\n- 2 cups water\n- juice of 1 fresh lemon (about 3 tablespoons)\n- 2-3 tablespoons raw honey\n- 1 star anise (optional)\n- 3-4 cloves (optional)\n- ¼ teaspoon turmeric\n- pinch of cayenne pepper (optional)\n- lemon slices for garnish\n- fresh mint leaves for garnish\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Bring water to a boil in a small saucepan. Add sliced ginger, star\nanise, and cloves if using. Reduce heat and simmer gently for 8-10\nminutes to extract full flavor.\n\n2. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, honey, turmeric, and\ncayenne if desired. Taste and adjust sweetness or lemon as preferred.\n\n3. Strain through a fine mesh sieve into two mugs, leaving as much ginger\nas you'd like in each cup.\n\n4. Garnish with fresh lemon slices and mint leaves. Serve immediately\nwhile steaming hot. Can be stored in the refrigerator and reheated, or\nenjoyed cold over ice on warmer days."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":828,"cache_read_input_tokens":108171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":828},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6b5fbce-18cb-479d-8d88-154976bac39e","uuid":"9a8a7f59-fd8e-49a4-b4ed-061bc31524a5"}
