{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0186JBHGpBd39ccPNzKF4AHw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HZDxoGmEyhAyNEowsWBbNC","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Apricot Preserve.generated.24.txt","content":"PAGE 156 — PRESERVES & JAMS\n\nApricot Preserve\n\nThis preserve captures the bright, sun-kissed essence of apricots at their\npeak. Makes 5-6 jars.\n\nEQUIPMENT NEEDED:\n- Large heavy-bottomed pot\n- Candy/jam thermometer\n- Glass jars, sterilized (500ml size)\n- Lids and rings (new rubber seals)\n\nINGRED--NTS:\n- 2kg fresh apricots, pitted and halved\n- 1.5kg preserving sugar (or reg-ular white sugar)\n- juice of 2 fresh lemons\n- 1 teaspoon butter\n- optional: ¼ teaspoon almond extr@ct\n- optional: 4-5 blanched almond kernels per jar\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\n1. Combine apricots, sugar, and lemon juice in a large pot. Let sit for\n2-3 hours (or overnight) to allow juices to release.\n\n2. Place pot over medium-high heat. Stir frequently until sugar dissolves\ncompletely. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring occasionally, for\n35-40 minutes until setting point is reached (104-105°C on a\nthermometer).\n\n3. Add butter near the end of cooking to reduce foam. Remove any scum\nwith a clean spoon.\n\n4. If using almond extract, add in final minute. Fill hot sterilized\njars, leaving 1cm headspace.\n\n5. Seal immediately, turn upside down for 2-3 minutes, then turn upright.\nCool completely before labeling. Preserve keeps for 12 months in a cool,\ndark cupboard once sealed properly."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":766,"cache_read_input_tokens":109615,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":766},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6b5fbce-18cb-479d-8d88-154976bac39e","uuid":"3da38503-c14c-4f73-bb10-7fcacc1879bc"}
